<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   Well, we aren't <I>afraid</I> of competition, but we do
respect it enough not to sit on our butts and never expand
the world of Norrath.  I don't think that competition has so
much to do with the ongoing development of the game,
though; I doubt that we'd let EverQuest stagnate if we
happened to be the only game in town (so to speak).  We
enjoy watching our world come to life as it can only by
being played by thousands of people.  Heck, I get a bigger
kick out of players' reactions to my work than I do when I
play the game myself.  As long as we at Verant Interactive
continue to take pleasure in the acts of creation that
EverQuest requires, and as long as people continue to have
fun using our product, then the game will continue to grow,
competitors or no competitors.<P>

