				Ladies and Gentlemen,<BR>
<BR>
  Milo is obviously a well-collected individual. He has character flaws just as many of us do. Due to one of his more prevalent character flaws he chooses to persecute those of lesser ability, mainly spelling and grammar, than himself. To compound that, he mercilessly targets the patrons of Verant Interactive. This leads to the illustration of one of his other blatantly obvious character flaws: Lack of customer service. Normally I wouldn't consider this a &quot;character flaw&quot; per-se. I do however in this instance due to the customer/vendor dynamic that exists which he utterly disregards to the extreme of his CEO's intervention. LOL! (Sorry I couldn't resist, that one's for you Milo) <BR>
  In closing, I actually enjoy Milo's envenomed prose. Milo has obviously done very well for himself in life and merely wants us all to know about it. What's so wrong with that? He is just seeking some kind of introvert competitive validation. <BR>
  So kudos to Verant for protecting their investment! Milo, rent some space on a webserver and start up your board again!<BR>
  G'day and safe travels!<BR>
<BR>
Good Riddance, 46 Necro - Lanys
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
